The paper focuses on the use of neural network learning models in intelligent transportation systems, specifically addressing the issue of overfitting in deep learning models. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of regularized learning models to address overfitting, which could also place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
